Holy Bible Privacy Policy
Last Updated: May 29, 2024
This Privacy Policy outlines the practices and policies governing the collection, use, and disclosure of personal information by the Holy Bible ("Holy Bible," "we," "us," or "our"). We value your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal information. Please read this Privacy Policy carefully to understand how we collect, use, and safeguard your data. By using Holy Bible, you consent to the terms outlined in this Privacy Policy.
Information we collect
1.1. Personal Information
Holy Bible does not collect or store any personal information that can identify you, such as your name, email address, or phone number.
1.2. Non-Personal Information
Holy Bible may collect non-personal information, such as device information (e.g., device type, model, operating system version), session and usage data, and anonymous analytics. This data is used for app performance monitoring, crash reporting, and improving the user experience.
How We Use Your Information
2.1. Personal Information
As Holy Bible does not collect personal information, we do not use or share it.
2.2. Non-Personal Information
We use non-personal information for the following purposes:
App Functionality:
To ensure the proper functioning of Holy Bible on your device.
App Improvement:
To analyze user behavior and app performance for continuous improvement and development.
Third-Party Services
Holy Bible may use third-party services, such as analytics tools and advertising networks. These services may collect non-personal information to provide us with insights and help support our app. We encourage you to review the privacy policies of these third-party providers to understand their data collection practices.
Data Security
We employ reasonable security measures to protect the data collected by Holy Bible. However, no data transmission or storage method is entirely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security. You use Holy Bible at your own risk.
Children's Privacy
Holy Bible is not intended for users under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect any personal information from children under the age of 13. If you believe that a child has provided us with personal information, please contact us, and we will take the necessary steps to delete the information.
Changes to this Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy to reflect changes in our data practices. Any updates will be posted on this page with a revised "Last Updated" date. We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically to stay informed about how we handle your data.
Contact Us
If you have any questions, concerns, or feedback regarding this Privacy Policy or the privacy practices of Holy Bible, please contact us at arildo@codeinlab.io.
By using Holy Bible, you agree to the terms and conditions outlined in this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree with this Privacy Policy, please refrain from using the app.
